  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'Q1) How do I restore the signal beacon?

    Approach the generator and
    Right-Click to start the sync. You must flip cards to find equivalent Fractions
    and Decimals (e.g. 1/2 and 0.5). Once you think the pair flipped is correct,
    click the ''Check'' button to confirm the match.


    Q2) I input only 1 Ore,
    and should only need 2 matches from 4 cards, why are there so many?

    The
    grid always displays 20 cards. If you input 1 Ore, you only need to find 2 pairs
    from all 10 pairs available.


    Q3) Is there a limit to how many times I can
    guess?

    Yes. You have as many extra chance as the oress you input. 1 ore
    input means you can get it wrong once, 5 ore input means you can get it wrong
    5 times.


    Q4) How much energy do I get?

    1 Ore input provides a maximum
    of 10% energy, provided you find the 2 corresponding pairs before time runs out.


'
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
